org.apache.commons.rdf.api

Class AbstractGraphTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.commons.rdf.api.AbstractGraphTest

  • public abstract class AbstractGraphTest
extends Object
    Test Graph implementation

    To add to your implementation's tests, create a subclass with a name ending in Test and provide createFactory() which minimally must support RDF.createGraph() and RDF.createIRI(String), but ideally support all operations.

    This test uses try-with-resources blocks for calls to Graph.stream() and Graph.iterate().

    See Also:
    Graph, RDF

      • whyJavaStreamsMightNotTakeOverFromSparql

        public void whyJavaStreamsMightNotTakeOverFromSparql()
                                              throws Exception
        An attempt to use the Java 8 streams to look up a more complicated query.

        FYI, the equivalent SPARQL version (untested): 

             SELECT ?orgName WHERE {
             ?org foaf:name ?orgName .
             ?alice foaf:member ?org .
             ?bob foaf:member ?org .
             ?alice foaf:knows ?bob .
           FILTER NOT EXIST { ?bob foaf:knows ?alice }
    }
        Throws:
        Exception - If test fails
